--- rweber221 <rweber221@...> wrote:

> Matlab 7.3 running Cantera 1.70 complains when I try to
> define a phase 
> using the ideal_solution keyword in cti file, as
> described in the 
> documentation for Cantera 1.50. The ct2ctml.log file
> contains the 
> following message:
> 
> ideal_solution(name="liquid",
> NameError: name 'ideal_solution' is not defined
> 
> The phases ideal_gas, stoichiometric_liquid and
> stoichiometric_solid do 
> seem to be recognized. While I would eventually like to
> be able to 
> equilibrate with a gas phase, at the moment, all I am
> looking for is 
> homogenous kinetics so is there any harm in just calling
> the condensed 
> phase an ideal gas?
> 
> Thanks,
> Bob Weber
